Xinhua Summary of Asia-Pacific Stocks News
The NZSE40 Index ended 7 points higher at 1,910 with a turnover of 39.2
million New Zealand dollars (16.5 million U.S. dollars).
Although market heavyweight Telecom was down 7 cents to 432 cents,
discount retailer the Warehouse rose 23 cents to 628 cents, Independent
Newspapers 15 to 335 cents, Auckland Airport 14 to 339 cents, and
financial giant Tower 13 to 518 cents.
----
TOKYO -- The 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average lost 179.81 points, or 1.69
percent, to close at 10,452.54.
The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all First Section
issues, also fell 15.70 points, or 1.44 percent, to close at 1,071.78.
Volume on the main section decreased to 502.14 million shares from
997.95 million last Friday.
----
SHENZHEN -- The Component Stock Index on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange
closed at 3,387.81 points Monday, up 3.11 points from the last close.
----
SHANGHAI -- The Composite Index on the Shanghai Stock Exchange closed
at 1,687.28 points Monday, down 4.04 points from the last close.
----
MANILA -- The 33-company main index, Phisix, flipped up by 22. 93
points, or 2.3 percent, to end at 1,040.80. The broader all- share
index, however, skid 1.60 points to 660.91.
Dealers traded 181.1 million shares worth 390.9 million pesos ( 7.6
million U.S. dollars) against Friday's 375.7 million shares worth 582.7
million pesos (11.3 million dollars).
----
BANGKOK -- The Stock Exchange of Thailand (SET) index on Monday lost
2.91 points to close at 282.06.
Some 178 million shares worth about 2.52 billion baht (57.29 million
U.S. dollars) changed hands.
----
CANBERRA -- The benchmark S&P 200 closed 26.1 points lower at 3, 199.0,
while the all ordinaries lost 25.1 points to 3,133.9.
National turnover reached 416.8 million shares worth 1.28 billion
Australian dollars (658.94 million U.S. dollars), with 473 stocks
rising, 537 falling and 274 steady.
----
KUALA LUMPUR -- The 100-quality stocks Composite Index rose 7. 58
points to 618.9, the Emas Index gained 1.31 points to 148.14, the
Second Board Index advanced 1.25 points to 117.58, the Technology Index
edged down 0.12 of a point to 42.28, and The Finance Index added 63.65
points to 4,624.44.
Total turnover stood at 147.25 million shares worth 218.2 million
ringgit (57.42 million U.S. dollars) against 179.86 million shares
valued at 358.22 million ringgit (94.26 million dollars) last Friday.
----
HONG KONG -- The benchmark Hang Seng Index shed 143.54 points, or 1.40
percent, to close at 10,130.59 points.
Turnover was a thin 5.375 billion HK dollars (689 million U.S.
dollars), sharply lower than Friday's 8.603 billion HK dollars (1. 103
billion dollar).
----
SINGAPORE -- Share prices edged up on the Singapore Stock Market Monday
with the benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gaining 4.54 points or 0.3
percent to end at 1,420.78 in thin dealing.
The total volume dropped to 140.64 million units valued at 247. 56
million Singapore dollars (about 136.55 million U.S. dollars). Losers
led gainers by 136 to 70 with 363 counters unchanged.
----
TAIPEI -- The Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) closed lower Monday, with
the weighted index, the market's key barometer, moving down 88.68
points to close at 3,712.82.
A total of 1.49 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover of
31.94 billion new Taiwan dollars (0.93 billion U.S. dollars), a
decrease from the previous trading session which saw 3. 04 billion
shares change hands on a market turnover of 72.31 billion new Taiwan
dollars (2.09 billion dollars).
